text: The 1989–90 Algerian Championnat National was the 28th season of the Algerian Championnat National since its establishment in 1962. A total of 16 teams contested the league, with JS Kabylie as the defending champions, The Championnat started on August 31, 1989. and ended on June 14, 1990. ==Team summaries== === Promotion and relegation === Teams promoted from Algerian Division 2 1989-1990 * CS Constantine * WA Tlemcen Teams relegated to Algerian Division 2 1990-1991 * RC Relizane * USM Alger ==League table== ==References== ==External links== *1989–90 Algerian Championnat National Algerian Championnat National Championnat National Category:Algerian Ligue Professionnelle 1 seasons
